# Day 42 – Personal Financial Command Center

## Objective
The objective of this project was to build an interactive Personal Financial Command Center that helps users understand, organize, and improve their financial health through a modern dashboard.
## Features
- Financial Overview Dashboard
- Income & Expense Tracking
- Budget Management
- Savings & Goal Planning
- Cash Flow Analysis
- Financial Health Score
- AI Financial Recommendations
- What-If Financial Simulator
- Interactive Charts & Progress Tracking
- Local Storage Support
- Printable Reports
- Responsive Dark Theme UI
## Technologies Used
- HTML5
- CSS3
- Vanilla JavaScript
- Local Storage API
## Key Learnings
- Designed an interactive financial dashboard.
- Implemented client-side financial calculations.
- Learned how to organize financial data visually.
- Improved UI/UX design for dashboards.
- Built an offline web application without backend services.
## Outcome
This project demonstrates how AI-assisted development can be used to create practical financial management tools using only frontend technologies.
